<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="quoteright" style="width:250px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:143.2%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/MIRAGE.jpg" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/MIRAGE.jpg" width="250" height="358"></div></div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p><em><strong>Mirage of Blaze</strong></em> is a light novel series written by Mizuna Kuwabara. It was adapted into a thirteen episode anime season in 2002. A three part OVA titled Rebels of the River Edge was released in 2004. The translation of the light novels can be found <a class="urllink" href="http://www.asphodelshaven.com/translations/novel">here<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></p><p>Ougi Takaya is a seventeen year old <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OrdinaryHighSchoolStudent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OrdinaryHighSchoolStudent">high school student</a> whose life changes drastically when he is attacked by a man with supernatural powers, a confrontation which awakens the same abilities in him. The man identifies himself as Naoe Nobutsuna and claims Takaya is Lord Kagetora, adopted son of Uesugi Kenshin whom he has sworn to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleButler" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleButler">serve</a>. He reveals that the source of their powers stems from the fact that they are Possessors, souls who have been possessing human bodies for over four hundred years.</p><p>With Kagetora as their leader, the Possessors have been fighting the Feudal Underworld, an army of vengeful spirits of samurai who fell during the Warring States era. Some of these spirits are also able to possess bodies and do so in order to restart the wars, this time to end them in their favor. Takaya has <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LaserGuidedAmnesia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LaserGuidedAmnesia">no memory of this</a> however and and refuses to believe he is Kagetora. As he begins to remember however, he becomes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TomatoIntheMirror" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TomatoIntheMirror">increasingly distraught</a> and begins to draw on Naoe for support, but Naoe is neither the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SexyMentor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SexyMentor">mentor</a> nor the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleButler" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleButler">convenient protector</a> Takaya thinks he is.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><p>One of the main themes that make Mirage of Blaze stand out is the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveMakesYouCrazy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveMakesYouCrazy">complicated</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BodyguardCrush" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BodyguardCrush">relationship</a> of Kagetora and Naoe.</p><hr><h2><em>Mirage of Blaze</em> provides examples of:</h2><p></p><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllTakeAndNoGive" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllTakeAndNoGive">All Take and No Give</a>: Kagetora and Naoe are this trope.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmbiguouslyGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmbiguouslyGay">Ambiguously Gay</a>: Kagetora, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> though by the end of the OVA, it's not ambiguous anymore as he has finally accepted Naoe as a potentional lover</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnguishedDeclarationOfLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnguishedDeclarationOfLove">Anguished Declaration of Love</a>: Naoe to Kagetora.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AsiaRuneChant" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AsiaRuneChant">Asia Rune Chant</a>: whenever the Possesors exorcize spirits or summon creatures or guardians.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwfulTruth" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwfulTruth">Awful Truth</a>: Naoe <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">is basically sitting on a ticking time bomb, he knows when Kagetora remembers that they'll fall back in their old pattern of hate and love</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadassBiker" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadassBiker">Badass Biker</a> / <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BikerBabe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BikerBabe">Biker Babe</a>: Haruie</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleButler" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleButler">Battle Butler</a>: Naoe.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Bishonen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Bishonen">Bish&#333;nen</a>: Kagetora, Naoe.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackAndGrayMorality" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackAndGrayMorality">Black-and-Gray Morality</a>: The spirits the protagonists are fighting against have entirely selfish aims at conquering the modern world, but as the series goes on, we find our main characters have some major skeletons in their closet as well.</li><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BodyguardCrush" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BodyguardCrush">Bodyguard Crush</a>: Naoe <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">has been madly in love with Kagetora for over four hundred years</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakTheCutie" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakTheCutie">Break the Cutie</a>: Kagetora<span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">'s adoptive father sent him off as a hostage of the Hojo, he was raped and then forced to commit seppuku to escape dishonor when the castle fell</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CherryBlossoms" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CherryBlossoms">Cherry Blossoms</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Incarnation of Takaya's corpse.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChessmaster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChessmaster">The Chessmaster</a>: Naoe, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> who manipulated both Kagetora's family and the Feudal Underworld to save Kagetora</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Cliffhanger" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Cliffhanger">Cliffhanger</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Naoe shot dead and Takaya going mad. Takaya kidnapping and kidnapping again. Nagahide's bodily death. Takaya removed from Uesugi clan. Naoe going over to Oda. Takaya's soul reaching near the limit.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreepyCrossdresser" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreepyCrossdresser">Creepy Crossdresser</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DrivenToSuicide" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DrivenToSuicide">Driven to Suicide</a>: Kagetora <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">when forced to commit seppuku</span>.<ul><li> Only some inversions <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Kagetora/Takaya attempts suicide in volume 20 when the mental and emotional tolls of everything he'd dealt with reaches a breaking point, but Naoe saves him. Also, Naoe had attempted suicide in the past but he'd kept this hidden from Kagetora.</span></li></ul></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DownerEnding" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DownerEnding">Downer Ending</a>: In order to stop Yami Sengoku, Kagetora is forced to use the last of his soul life. Not only does this kill Kagetora/Takaya, but this <em>prevents him from ever reincarnating again</em>. He lives long enough to <em>finally</em> confess his love to Naoe before he dies in the latter's arms. Naoe put in his own breast the Takaya's broken nearly soul. Takaya's soul seemed pounded but freezes in him. He decided to stay alive repeat the possession until the limit of his own soul in order to prove the eternal love to Takaya.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheFourGods" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheFourGods">The Four Gods</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenderBender" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenderBender">Gender Bender</a><ul><li> Haruie <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">is a male Possessor who's using a woman's body</span>.</li><li> Also Kagetora <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">who was forced to possess the body of his lover, effectively turning into a woman</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HardDrinkingPartyGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HardDrinkingPartyGirl">Hard-Drinking Party Girl</a>: Haruie</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HufflepuffHouse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HufflepuffHouse">Hufflepuff House</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> The Oda clan. They play a fairly significant role in the backstory of the series are implied to an extremely powerful faction, with Kagetora having died in a previous battle against them, and in the <em>Rebels of the Rivers Edge</em> OVA, it's stated that numerous other clans formed a coalition against them, but we never actually anybody from the Oda clan in the series. Likewise, the coalition against Oda doesn't get much focus.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HistoricalDomainCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HistoricalDomainCharacter">Historical Domain Character</a>: Uesugi Kagetora, Naoe Nobutsuna, Haruie Kakizaki, Yasuda Nagahide, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/UesugiKenshin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/UesugiKenshin">Uesugi Kenshin</a>, Houjou Ujiyasu, Houjou Ujimasa, Houjou Ujiteru, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/TakedaShingen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/TakedaShingen">Takeda Shingen</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/DateMasamune" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/DateMasamune">Date Masamune</a>, Date Kojirou</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IAmWho" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IAmWho">I Am Who?</a>: Kagetora <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">is the leader and the strongest of the Possesors</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IDidWhatIHadToDo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IDidWhatIHadToDo">I Did What I Had to Do</a>: Naoe is willing to do <em>anything</em> for Kagetora, and has proved it repeatedly.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IfICantHaveYou" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IfICantHaveYou">If I Can't Have You...</a>: Naoe <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">is prepared to kill Kagetora and himself so that Kagetora will "never belong to anyone else"</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Immortality" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Immortality">Immortality</a>: The Possessors</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntimateHealing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntimateHealing">Intimate Healing</a>: Naoe <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> right before ending the spell that was keeping Kagetora's soulless body alive, used what looked like a farewell kiss to pass Kagetora another <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProtectiveCharm" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProtectiveCharm">Protective Charm</a>, effectively saving him</span>.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntimatePsychotherapy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntimatePsychotherapy">Intimate Psychotherapy</a>: When Naoe and Kagetora <em>finally</em> consummate their relationship in volume 20, it's in the aftermath of Kagetora being horribly betrayed, receiving a death curse on his eye, and a suicide attempt. The sex allows Kagetora to see the toll Naoe's love has had on his own body&mdash;from a hideous scar on his chest from having protected Kagetora, to seeing scars of Naoe's <em>own</em> suicide attempts over his love for Kagetora.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JidaiGeki" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JidaiGeki">Jidaigeki</a>: The many flashbacks of the Possessors' past lives.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Keigo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Keigo">Keigo</a>: Kagetora-sama indeed.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LaserGuidedAmnesia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LaserGuidedAmnesia">Laser-Guided Amnesia</a>: Kagetora, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">unable to handle the pain of his lover's death and Naoe's part in it, choses to forget everything</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveMakesYouCrazy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveMakesYouCrazy">Love Makes You Crazy</a> / <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveMakesYouEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveMakesYouEvil">Love Makes You Evil</a>: Naoe</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ManlyTears" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ManlyTears">Manly Tears</a>: Naoe and Kagetora during Naoe's breakdown.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MayDecemberRomance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MayDecemberRomance">May&#150;December Romance</a>: Kagetora and Naoe, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> subverted as Naoe's body is eleven years older than Takaya's, but their souls are both hundreds of years old</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderTheHypotenuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderTheHypotenuse">Murder the Hypotenuse</a>: When Naoe <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">forces Kagetora to possess the body of his lover</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MyGodWhatHaveIDone" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MyGodWhatHaveIDone">My God, What Have I Done?</a>: Naoe <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">after <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NearRapeExperience" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NearRapeExperience">nearly raping</a> Kagetora, but then again, who wouldn't crack after four hundred years of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllTakeAndNoGive" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllTakeAndNoGive">mental</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnresolvedSexualTension" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnresolvedSexualTension">torture</a></span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NearRapeExperience" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NearRapeExperience">Near-Rape Experience</a>: Naoe and Kagetora.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurGhostsAreDifferent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurGhostsAreDifferent">Our Ghosts Are Different</a>: Aside from vengeful spirits, there also exist guardian spirits who are bound to a single place.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurSoulsAreDifferent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurSoulsAreDifferent">Our Souls Are Different</a>: The Possessors <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> who are able to break the reincarnation cycle by possessing human bodies. Of course this is a <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralEventHorizon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralEventHorizon">really bad thing to do</a>, but they <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IDidWhatIHadToDo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IDidWhatIHadToDo">do what they have to</a></span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParentalAbandonment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParentalAbandonment">Parental Abandonment</a>: Kagetora <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> who got sent off as a hostage by his father during the Warring States era, and in the present his father abandons him again, preparing to sacrifice his soul for the "greater good"</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerGlows" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerGlows">Power Glows</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProtectiveCharm" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProtectiveCharm">Protective Charm</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RapeAsBackstory" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RapeAsBackstory">Rape as Backstory</a>: Kagetora</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedemptionEqualsDeath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedemptionEqualsDeath">Redemption Equals Death</a>: Houjou Ujiteru <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">turning on Ujimasa and allowing himself to be exorcised by Kagetora to save him</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReincarnationRomance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReincarnationRomance">Reincarnation Romance</a>: Naoe and Kagetora, and also Haruie <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> who is looking for his long-lost lover, thought it's not technically reincarnation as they escape the cycle of rebirth by by possessing bodies</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SarcasticDevotee" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SarcasticDevotee">Sarcastic Devotee</a>: Naoe who mocks Kagetora's weakness, Haruie, and Nagahide who's borderline insubordinate.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SayMyName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SayMyName">Say My Name</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScaryShinyGlasses" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScaryShinyGlasses">Scary Shiny Glasses</a>: Chiaki</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SexyMentor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SexyMentor">Sexy Mentor</a>: Naoe, in the beginning, subverted <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">when he angrily tells Kagetora he is <em>not</em> a mentor nor a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleButler" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleButler">convenient protector</a></span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SingleTargetSexuality" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SingleTargetSexuality">Single-Target Sexuality</a>: Naoe has only ever loved Kagetora.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmokingIsCool" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmokingIsCool">Smoking Is Cool</a> / <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmokingIsGlamorous" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmokingIsGlamorous">Smoking Is Glamorous</a>: Naoe, especially in the OVA.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SnowMeansLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SnowMeansLove">Snow Means Love</a>: The end of the OVA.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SparklingStreamOfTears" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SparklingStreamOfTears">Sparkling Stream of Tears</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StraightGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StraightGay">Straight Gay</a>: Naoe and Takaya.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TomatoInTheMirror" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TomatoInTheMirror">Tomato in the Mirror</a>: Kagetora <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> who is not the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OrdinaryHighSchoolStudent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OrdinaryHighSchoolStudent">Ordinary High-School Student</a> he thought he was but in reality an ancient warlord of the Warring States era who's possessed the body of a boy, ousting his soul in the process</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TroubledButCute" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TroubledButCute">Troubled, but Cute</a>: Takaya.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrueCompanions" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrueCompanions">True Companions</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UncomfortableElevatorMoment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UncomfortableElevatorMoment">Uncomfortable Elevator Moment</a>: More so for Kagetora than Naoe.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnresolvedSexualTension" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnresolvedSexualTension">Unresolved Sexual Tension</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Four hundred years of it too, no wonder Naoe has reached his breaking point. Still he initially manages to mask his feelings for Kagetora perfectly, but when Kagetora dreams of his lover's death, Naoe realizes he will soon remember everything and drops the act. Naoe eventually snaps and forces himself on Kagetora, the event triggering Kagetora's memory of how he was raped while a hostage. It serves as a wake-up call for Naoe, who goes into <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MyGodWhatHaveIDone" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MyGodWhatHaveIDone">shock mode</a> when he realizes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NearRapeExperience" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NearRapeExperience">what he almost did</a>.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatBeautifulEyes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatBeautifulEyes">What Beautiful Eyes!</a>: Naoe comments on the brilliance of Kagetora's eyes.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YaoiGenre" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YaoiGenre">Yaoi Genre</a></li></ul><hr>
</div>
<div class="alt-titles section section-fact">
